My favourite rainbows are the ones that appear after a summer shower in the garden. They do not stay long, just a few minutes, but they are magical.

First, the sky turns grey and the rain taps on the window. Then, the clouds part and the sun peeks out. Suddenly, a big, bright arc stretches across the sky. It has seven colours: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, and violet.

I love the green one the most. It looks like a patch of fresh grass floating in the air. Sometimes, I think a leprechaun is hiding behind it, waiting to give me a pot of gold. But when I run outside, the rainbow is gone.

It is a secret gift from the sky. It makes me smile and reminds me that even after a storm, the sun always comes back. I wish I could catch one in a jar, but it is better to just watch it dance in the wet air. It is the most beautiful thing in the whole world. [end of text]


